 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 6.84,
   "text": "In China, 5-2-0 means I love you, but 2-5-0 means you idiot, and there's a lot more"
  },
  {
   "start": 6.84,
   "end": 8.68,
   "text": "hidden in the language, why does that work?"
  },
  {
   "start": 9.14,
   "end": 13.44,
   "text": "Because Chinese is full of words that sound almost exactly like numbers, so people started"
  },
  {
   "start": 13.44,
   "end": 18.06,
   "text": "using strings of numbers as code, something you can text, comment, or even put on a gift."
  },
  {
   "start": 18.56,
   "end": 24.98,
   "text": "A few digits standing in for a whole phrase, say 5-2-0 fast, wu-er-ling, and it sounds"
  },
  {
   "start": 24.98,
   "end": 27.18,
   "text": "like wu-ai-ni, I love you."
  },
  {
   "start": 27.18,
   "end": 32.12,
   "text": "It's so well known that May 20th, written 5-20, has become an unofficial romance day"
  },
  {
   "start": 32.12,
   "end": 39.82,
   "text": "like a second valentine's, add 1-3-1-4, which sounds like forever, a lifetime, and 5-2-0-1-3-1-4"
  },
  {
   "start": 39.82,
   "end": 43.1,
   "text": "means I'll love you forever, but the same trick cuts the other way."
  },
  {
   "start": 43.68,
   "end": 49.26,
   "text": "Call someone a 2-5-0, or buy wu, and you've called them a fool, and there's more, 8-8"
  },
  {
   "start": 49.26,
   "end": 50.24,
   "text": "sounds like bye-bye."
  },
  {
   "start": 50.7,
   "end": 55.22,
   "text": "6-6-6 means you're a legend, seriously skilled, a few digits can carry an entire"
  },
  {
   "start": 55.22,
   "end": 59.64,
   "text": "mood, so a string of numbers in a chinese chat might be a maths problem, or a love letter,"
  },
  {
   "start": 59.92,
   "end": 64.88,
   "text": "or an insult, one block of numbers, two completely different worlds, want to actually start learning"
  },
  {
   "start": 64.88,
   "end": 69.92,
   "text": "chinese, discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io"
  }
